                        <div class="container_12">
                            <strong><center>
                                    <h2>What is the&nbsp;<kbd>ThreadLocal</kbd>&nbsp;class? How and why would you use it?</h2>
                                </center></strong>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <col class="pg-empty-placeholder"> 
                    <h3> <form class="form-horizontal"> 
</form> </h3> 
                    <h1></h1>
                    <div class="clearfix clear-columns"></div>
                    <div class="clearfix clear-columns"></div>
                    <div class="clearfix clear-columns"></div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <label> 
                                <input class="control-label" type="checkbox" value="">        Mark answer as correct &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
                            </label>
                            <h3>Answer 1</h3> 
                            <p>A single&nbsp;<a href="http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/ThreadLocal.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; min-height: 0px; min-width: 0px; color: rgb(57, 118, 203); font-family: 'Proxima Nova', Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15.6px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; line-height: 23.4px; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><code style="margin: 0px; padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(238, 238, 238); vertical-align: text-bottom; min-height: 0px; min-width: 0px; border-radius: 3px; display: inline-block; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.8em; line-height: 1em; max-width: 100%; background: rgb(255, 255, 252);">ThreadLocal</code></a>&nbsp;instance can store different values for each thread independently. Each thread that accesses the&nbsp;<code style="margin: 0px; padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(238, 238, 238); vertical-align: text-bottom; min-height: 0px; min-width: 0px; border-radius: 3px; display: inline-block; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.8em; line-height: 1em; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-variant-ligatures: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background: rgb(255, 255, 252);">get()</code>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<code style="margin: 0px; padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(238, 238, 238); vertical-align: text-bottom; min-height: 0px; min-width: 0px; border-radius: 3px; display: inline-block; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.8em; line-height: 1em; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-variant-ligatures: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background: rgb(255, 255, 252);">set()</code>&nbsp;method of a&nbsp;<code style="margin: 0px; padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(238, 238, 238); vertical-align: text-bottom; min-height: 0px; min-width: 0px; border-radius: 3px; display: inline-block; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.8em; line-height: 1em; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-variant-ligatures: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background: rgb(255, 255, 252);">ThreadLocal</code>&nbsp;instance is accessing its own, independently initialized copy of the variable.&nbsp;<code style="margin: 0px; padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(238, 238, 238); vertical-align: text-bottom; min-height: 0px; min-width: 0px; border-radius: 3px; display: inline-block; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.8em; line-height: 1em; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-variant-ligatures: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background: rgb(255, 255, 252);">ThreadLocal</code>instances are typically private static fields in classes that wish to associate state with a thread (e.g., a user ID or transaction ID). The example below, from the&nbsp;<a href="http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/ThreadLocal.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; min-height: 0px; min-width: 0px; color: rgb(57, 118, 203); font-family: 'Proxima Nova', Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15.6px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; line-height: 23.4px; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><code style="margin: 0px; padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(238, 238, 238); vertical-align: text-bottom; min-height: 0px; min-width: 0px; border-radius: 3px; display: inline-block; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.8em; line-height: 1em; max-width: 100%; background: rgb(255, 255, 252);">ThreadLocal</code>&nbsp;Javadoc</a>, generates unique identifiers local to each thread. A threadâ€™s id is assigned the first time it invokes&nbsp;<code style="margin: 0px; padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(238, 238, 238); vertical-align: text-bottom; min-height: 0px; min-width: 0px; border-radius: 3px; display: inline-block; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.8em; line-height: 1em; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-variant-ligatures: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background: rgb(255, 255, 252);">ThreadId.get()</code>&nbsp;and remains unchanged on subsequent calls.<br></p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <label>
                                <input class="control-label" type="checkbox" value="">&nbsp;Mark answer as correct &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
                            </label>
                            <h3>Answer 2</h3> 
                            <pre style="margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; min-height: 0px; min-width: 0px; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-variant-ligatures: normal; line-height: 20px; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><code style="margin: 0px; padding: 2px 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(238, 238, 238); vertical-align: text-bottom; min-height: 0px; min-width: 0px; border-radius: 3px; display: inline-block; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.9em; line-height: 1.5em; max-width: 100%; width: 893px; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(255, 255, 252);">public class ThreadId {
    // Next thread ID to be assigned
    private static final AtomicInteger nextId = new AtomicInteger(0);
    // Thread local variable containing each thread's ID
    private static final ThreadLocal&lt;Integer&gt; threadId =
        new ThreadLocal&lt;Integer&gt;() {
            @Override protected Integer initialValue() {
                return nextId.getAndIncrement();
        }
    };
    // Returns the current thread's unique ID, assigning it if necessary
    public static int get() {
        return threadId.get();
    }
}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <label>
                                <input class="control-label" type="checkbox" value="">&nbsp;Mark answer as correct &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
                            </label>
                            <h3></h3>
                            <h3 style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">Answer 3</h3> 
                            <p>Each thread holds an implicit reference to its copy of a thread-local variable as long as the thread is alive and the ThreadLocal instance is accessible; after a thread goes away, all of its copies of thread-local instances are subject to garbage collection (unless other references to these copies exist).<br></p>
